Review: muppets remake where the only human actor is patrick dempsey

all of this ruined because johnny refused to read the airline flight requirements before boarding... you get one small carry-on and a personal item per passenger! if he had just read ahead of time, he could have shoved that 2 million in a small duffel and a roller bag easy! learn how to travel my guy
the sound design in this needs to be recognized immediately and at the highest level.
don’t think I’ve watched this all the way through since 2005 so imagine my surprise when I found out this is 80 mins INCLUDING CREDITS what an achievement in cinema & animation

kind of the perfect movie adaptation of the musical because all of my least favorite parts of the musical were way better in the movie and all of my least favorite parts of the movie were way better in the musical
joker this joker that what we don’t talk about is that rupert pupkin is really a disruptor okay? if u don’t like the industry be the change you want to see etc

the west wing of its time (that is to say, impossible to watch in 20 years without feeling both extreme admiration for artistic achievement and extreme frustration for hardcore missing the point). that said i would not be who i am today (for better or worse) without this musical so it gets points for that at least

full disclosure i did not finish this in one, two or even three sittings. I had to watch this in 20 min increments over several days because of how heavy this story is & how effective the filmmaking is in making the audience feel the horror and dread an hopelessness that the survivors of the crash must have felt. would love to see this in a theater one day if ever give a chance - cannot imagine how the plane crash and the huge expanses of white void play on a big screen.
captures something really lovely in the idea that there is intimacy in grief and even just muddling through is something to be proud of
long-haired kevin bacon saving lives in that wild museum/hospital/church is peak cinema
